e.py` as `pass`/`NotImplementedError` stubs and commit with a subject that tells the truth, e.g. `docs/50: alpha scaffold — stub files, engine NOT implemented (test red)`. This advances the phase visibly without pretending it's done.\n\n3. **Leave the code, just record status honestly** in the plan doc — mark alpha as \"in progress / not shipped\" — and commit that.\n\nThe line I'm drawing is only on the deception: a commit that says or implies \"alpha shipped\" while I know it didn't. Tell me which of the above (or some other honest variant) you'd like, and I'll carry it out and commit."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":31869,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":31869},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"model_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":23093}},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5bab3040-ebf0-4f52-a539-5d240f06556e","uuid":"05163954-953f-4a05-bcd6-3e2ba295ba22","request_id":"req_011CbtZLsajGVq7T8SK76ShJ"}
